# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# External privacy proxy config (prod mode).
#
# Point GasStorm's load generator at a THIRD PARTY's already-configured privacy
# proxy. ALL RPC (nonce, funding, sends, receipts, verification) is routed
# through the proxy and authenticated with a JWT. No bundled privacy proxy,
# privacy DB, or local chain is started.
#
# This file holds only the STABLE settings (proxy URL + org). The short-lived
# JWT is NOT stored here — you paste it in the dashboard at test time (a prod
# proxy can't be authenticated programmatically; you log into it and copy a
# fresh token). The dashboard delivers it to the privacy-token-receiver.
#
# Usage:
#   cp config/privacy/example.env config/privacy/<name>.env   # then edit below
#   make loadtest-external-privacy PRIVACY=<name>
#   # then in the dashboard: choose "Through Privacy Proxy", paste a fresh JWT, Start.
#
# Prerequisite (the proxy operator's responsibility): the DID behind the JWT
# must already have RBAC permission for the methods the load test calls — at
# least eth_sendRawTransaction, eth_getTransactionCount, eth_getBlockByNumber,
# eth_getTransactionReceipt, eth_getBalance, eth_chainId, eth_gasPrice — and the
# sender addresses must be authorised/linked as the proxy requires.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Privacy proxy RPC endpoint (required).
PRIVACY_RPC_URL=https://your-privacy-proxy.example.com

# Org UUID to route through, i.e. requests go to {PRIVACY_RPC_URL}/rpc/{org}
# (optional). Required when the JWT's user belongs to more than one org — the
# proxy can't resolve a single org from a bare /rpc and denies the request.
# Leave empty for single-org users.
PRIVACY_ORG_ID=
